<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idcfc3ceb6-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0" identifier="/us/usc/t48/s2004"><num value="2004">§ 2004.</num><heading> Administrative matters</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idcfc3ceb7-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0" identifier="/us/usc/t48/s2004/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> Administrative support</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary of the Interior shall provide all necessary administrative support to accomplish the requirements of sections 2002 and 2003 of this title.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idcfc3ceb8-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0" identifier="/us/usc/t48/s2004/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Authorization of appropriations</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There are authorized to be appropriated such sums as may be necessary to carry out the provisions of this chapter.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idcfc3ceb9-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0">(<ref href="/us/pl/99/239/tIII/s304">Pub. L. 99–239, title III, § 304</ref>, <date date="1986-01-14">Jan. 14, 1986</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/99/1837">99 Stat. 1837</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
